{"id":"flood","term":"Flood","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>An event recorded in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 7\">Gen. 7</a> and 8. (See DELUGE.) In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 24:2\">Josh. 24:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 24:3\">3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 24:14\">14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 24:15\">15</a>, the word “flood” (R.V., “river”) means the river Euphrates. In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 66:6\">Ps. 66:6</a>, this word refers to the river Jordan.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 7","Joshua 24:2","Joshua 24:3","Joshua 24:14","Joshua 24:15","Psalms 66:6"]}